default2. Each Panel has £53,000 of funding from the Home Office to support its Police and Crime Panel. I understand this figure was arrived at from the average funding required, with on-costs, to appoint a scrutiny officer.  Whilst I can see the logic of this in terms of setting a national budget referencing ‘market testing’ and comparative value for money, it bears no relation 
