defaultConclusion.
defaultIn the final analysis, it is the effectiveness of the police force and the level of crime and disorder that matters most.  I have seen nothing 
defaultin this new governance arrangement 
defaultthat raises either the general public
default’s
default perception of the police or the public’s expectations
default 
defaultof them.
default&#xa0;
defaultIn fact I believe
default 
defaultbecause of 
defaultthe adverse publicity some of the 
defaultPCCs
default’ antics have
default attracted, and as the public do tend, unfairly and unfortunately, to 
default‘lump them all together’, 
defaultthe 
defaultpublic confidence in the Police Force is lower now that it has been for some time.  That in itself is not only a very worrying aspect but also, more critically, makes 
defaultthe job of the police more difficult than it would otherwise be and 
defaultcrime reduction itself much more difficult to achieve.
default&#xa0;
defaultAs it seems unlikely the governance arrangements will be abolished, it requires some serious amendment and fine tuning in the light of the experience and evidence.
